    "One of these papers explores the evolution of retail, starting from traditional methods and progressing to digital platforms, as well as its further progression into Metaverse retail (Bourlakis et al. 2009); the other paper proposes a typology of virtual store environment based on an in-depth investigation of 27 stores within Second Life (Hassouneh and Brengman 2015).",
    "Thus, they study the prevailing status quo and try to draw conclusions that indicate a general success.",
    "The author keywords co-occurrence analysis provides insights into the associated topics that have been mainly dealt with in the Metaverse, as well as the evolution of 1 3",
